cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

This paper discusses the energy efficiency of massive MIMO systems, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), networking and communications (cs.NI), control systems (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and architecture (cs.AR). The focus on optimizing transmit power and considering channel estimation and pilot contamination also suggests a strong connection to information theory and networking. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.SY, cs.MM, and cs.AR.
